Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.22,0:06:02.22,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ike Nwala
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.44,0:06:04.86,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Please tell us your scary story
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.42,0:06:13.32,Normal,,0,0,0,,This story is from the state of Wisconsin
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.54,0:06:15.46,Normal,,0,0,0,,And it's about a little girl
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.88,0:06:18.43,Normal,,0,0,0,,So, there was this girl called Jane
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:23.53,Normal,,0,0,0,,She used to wear a yellow ribbon around her neck everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.72,0:06:28.32,Normal,,0,0,0,,She knew a guy named Johnny, he was her best friend
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.87,0:07:24.06,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,0)\pos(261,948)}Yellow ribbon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:34.54,Normal,,0,0,0,,Everyday Johnny asked Jane:\N"why do you wear that yellow ribbon?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.54,0:06:37.24,Normal,,0,0,0,,But Jane would never reply to that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.60,0:06:41.44,Normal,,0,0,0,,When they grew up and became adults, they eventually got married
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.44,0:06:45.42,Normal,,0,0,0,,Jane gave birth to a baby, and he always asked her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:49.62,Normal,,0,0,0,,"Mama, why do you always wear that\Nyellow ribbon around your neck?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.96,0:06:52.02,Normal,,0,0,0,,But his mom never replied to that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.54,0:06:55.78,Normal,,0,0,0,,As time went by, Jane and Johnny became old
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.16,0:06:59.68,Normal,,0,0,0,,And one day Jane became ill
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.68,0:07:03.44,Normal,,0,0,0,,Johnny went to the hospital everyday to check her
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:05.88,Normal,,0,0,0,,And he asked her again
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.88,0:07:08.10,Normal,,0,0,0,,"Please, Jane, tell me"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.42,0:07:11.78,Normal,,0,0,0,,"Why do you always wear that yellow ribbon?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.78,0:07:13.96,Normal,,0,0,0,,Jane replied "you can have it"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.96,0:07:15.18,Normal,,0,0,0,,"Take it away"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.12,0:07:19.86,Normal,,0,0,0,,As Johnny unfastened the ribbon from her neck
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.86,0:07:21.86,Normal,,0,0,0,,Jane's head fell off
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.28,0:07:24.24,Normal,,0,0,0,,That's the story
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:33.24,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(714,934)}What a dynamic punch line!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.60,0:07:31.80,Endo,,0,0,0,,Really
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.54,0:07:33.54,Hamada,,0,0,0,,That was sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.54,0:07:35.84,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,The ending is so dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.84,0:07:38.24,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.42,0:07:38.24,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.24,0:07:41.58,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,928)}I don't think there are stories like this one in Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.42,0:07:40.24,Hosei,,0,0,0,,Nope
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:43.08,Hosei,,0,0,0,,I mean, they don't usually
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.66,0:07:41.94,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You're right
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.08,0:07:47.45,Hosei,,0,0,0,,End with a {\c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\pos(720,916)}black humor{\r} feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.72,0:07:47.45,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You're right
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.45,0:07:49.86,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It was easy to follow, I liked that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.86,0:07:51.66,Hosei,,0,0,0,,Was it effective for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.66,0:07:52.32,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:55.79,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(718.5,932)}You can tell it's from the U.S.A.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:54.30,Hosei,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.30,0:07:55.79,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,And that makes me wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.79,0:07:58.56,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(855,928)}Maybe we didn't need Agnes to join us
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.58,0:07:59.28,Endo,,0,0,0,,No way
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.28,0:08:01.97,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,She's from Hong Kong, it's different
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.44,0:08:01.97,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Of course we needed her
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.97,0:08:03.00,Hosei,,0,0,0,,But her face...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:05.70,Hamada,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,250)\pos(789,932)}That's just for show
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.10,0:08:10.00,Normal,,0,0,0,,Our next scary story is from Egypt
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.36,0:08:21.56,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Our representative from Egypt is miss Fifi
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.78,0:08:21.92,Other2,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,0)\pos(774,904)}Fifi
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.78,0:08:21.92,Other2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HBABAB8&\bord3\shad0\3c&H000000&\fade(250,0)\pos(784.5,788)}Egypt Representative
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.28,0:08:27.72,Normal,,0,0,0,,Egypt is the home of countless myths about pharaohs and curses
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.29,0:08:31.90,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,0)\3c&H010053&\pos(682.5,912)}Egypt
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:31.90,Normal,,0,0,0,,Which scary story are we going to listen to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.09,0:08:31.90,Other3,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\move(1000.5,590,862.5,590,16,9785)}Which scary story...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.52,0:08:37.72,Normal,,0,0,0,,I think you all already know this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.72,0:08:44.18,Normal,,0,0,0,,But if we talk about Egypt you can easily picture stories of pharaohs such as Tutankhamon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.18,0:08:48.86,Normal,,0,0,0,,Such as myths about cobras attacking you if you get close to a pharaoh's tomb
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.86,0:08:51.60,Normal,,0,0,0,,There are lots of stories like this one
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.60,0:08:58.70,Normal,,0,0,0,,I wanna tell you about a scary story I personally experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:03.49,Normal,,0,0,0,,Since when I was a little girl, I used to see white dwarfs all around
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.49,0:09:05.38,Normal,,0,0,0,,White dwarfs
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.30,0:09:05.38,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Dwarfs?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.38,0:09:07.16,Normal,,0,0,0,,I don't think I was the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:12.34,Normal,,0,0,0,,But since I was little, whenever I saw a white dwarf, something good would happen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.67,0:11:10.79,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,0)\pos(214.5,942)}White dwarf
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.34,0:09:16.02,Normal,,0,0,0,,It was a long time ago, from when I was a high schooler
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.02,0:09:18.88,Normal,,0,0,0,,That day I thought "it's been a while since I last saw one"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.34,0:09:20.66,Normal,,0,0,0,,And then
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.00,0:09:23.02,Normal,,0,0,0,,The doorbell rang
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:28.78,Normal,,0,0,0,,When I opened it there were around 50 men carrying vegetables
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:33.42,Normal,,0,0,0,,I recently moved in, so they were bringing me presents
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.62,0:09:35.18,Normal,,0,0,0,,So something good {\i1}did {\i0}happen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.18,0:09:40.06,Normal,,0,0,0,,Whenever I happened to see another white dwarf, the doorbell rang
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.06,0:09:42.38,Normal,,0,0,0,,And people brought me sweets
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.58,0:09:48.14,Normal,,0,0,0,,But one day I was busy making a phone call and the doorbell rang
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.14,0:09:50.96,Normal,,0,0,0,,I was too bothered to go open the door
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.96,0:09:56.08,Normal,,0,0,0,,That night I had a dream in which I was in the same room I was in during the day
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:59.66,Normal,,0,0,0,,There was a door on the other side, and from its gap
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:03.48,Normal,,0,0,0,,I could see a black dwarf behind it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.48,0:10:07.70,Normal,,0,0,0,,Its eyes were gleaming and it was staring at me blankly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.29,0:10:09.86,Normal,,0,0,0,,Then I suddenly opened my eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.36,0:10:14.14,Normal,,0,0,0,,I stared at that same door in my dream
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.63,0:10:19.54,Normal,,0,0,0,,And one of my neighbors was spying on me from that gap
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.54,0:10:23.50,Normal,,0,0,0,,I got frightened, but before I realized that man got closer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.50,0:10:28.50,Normal,,0,0,0,,And he started choking me with a really menacing look
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.50,0:10:32.46,Normal,,0,0,0,,He kept on pressing until I passed out
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.68,0:10:34.36,Normal,,0,0,0,,The next day I woke up, it was a dream
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.36,0:10:37.64,Normal,,0,0,0,,I was talking to the landlord and told him I had this weird dream
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.64,0:10:42.93,Normal,,0,0,0,,I told him that nice man from that house which often comes over was choking me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.93,0:10:46.10,Normal,,0,0,0,,He replied "no one lives in that house"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.90,0:10:49.32,Normal,,0,0,0,,"You're kidding me, aren't you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.32,0:10:52.68,Normal,,0,0,0,,He told me "no, it's true", and took me there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.20,0:10:54.98,Normal,,0,0,0,,He opened up the front door
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.98,0:10:57.40,Normal,,0,0,0,,And there really was nothing inside
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.40,0:11:01.74,Normal,,0,0,0,,It was still morning and I had no idea\Nwhat I just saw the night before
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:08.62,Normal,,0,0,0,,I got near the washstand and when I glanced at the mirror, I noticed I had a mark around my neck
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.32,0:11:10.79,Normal,,0,0,0,,The end
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.94,0:11:17.43,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,What do you think about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.68,0:11:20.33,Normal,,0,0,0,,More than "white dwarf", I'd say "small dwarf"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.38,0:11:20.33,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You know
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:26.17,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I thought you said {\pos(720,924)\3c&H000000&\blur3}shiroi koibito{\r} at first
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.22,0:11:26.40,Endo,,0,0,0,,That sweet from Hokkaido?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.18,0:11:26.40,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It's a traditional Hokkaido biscuit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.22,0:11:31.42,Normal,,0,0,0,,Next up is a scary story from Guinea, Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:40.88,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Our representative from Guinea is mr. Sankhon Ousmane
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:42.55,Other2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(760.5,930)}Sankhon Ousmane
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:42.55,Other2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HBABAB8&\bord3\shad0\3c&H000000&\pos(778.5,828)}Guinea Representative
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.66,0:11:55.30,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H010053&\fade(250,0)\pos(663,914)}Guinea
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.74,0:11:48.22,Normal,,0,0,0,,Guinea occupies the western edge of Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:54.62,Normal,,0,0,0,,And lots of different tribes live in its vast pristine nature: which story are we going to listen to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.49,0:11:55.30,Other3,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\move(1000.5,590,862.5,590,16,9785)}Which scary story...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:12:00.18,Normal,,0,0,0,,This story...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.52,0:12:05.84,Normal,,0,0,0,,It's a fairly popular scary story in Guinea,\Nwhich is in western Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.14,0:12:07.88,Normal,,0,0,0,,It's about a funeral
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:10.90,Normal,,0,0,0,,In Guinea, when someone dies
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.62,0:12:13.35,Normal,,0,0,0,,We bury them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.35,0:12:16.74,Normal,,0,0,0,,You burn your dead in Japan, we bury ours in Guinea
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.72,0:12:20.29,Other3,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)\pos(720,920)\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}In Guinea, they usually bury their dead
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.06,0:12:25.18,Normal,,0,0,0,,As a tradition, from when the dead is placed inside the coffin\Nuntil the burial is completed, you must not turn around
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.26,0:13:25.22,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,0)\pos(367.5,942)}Don't turn around
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.64,0:12:32.32,Normal,,0,0,0,,That's because it will disturb its ghost.\NSo, one day an eminent man died
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.76,0:12:34.64,Normal,,0,0,0,,And after his burial
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:39.08,Normal,,0,0,0,,Everyone thought it was time to go home, but one man
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.70,0:12:44.26,Normal,,0,0,0,,Was being pulled by something from behind
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.92,0:12:47.34,Normal,,0,0,0,,Something kept on pulling him
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.82,0:12:50.28,Normal,,0,0,0,,But no one could turn around to see it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.62,0:12:52.64,Normal,,0,0,0,,And for half a day
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.64,0:12:56.28,Normal,,0,0,0,,He stood still, quibering
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.83,0:12:58.39,Hamada,,0,0,0,,{\pos(969,642)}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.24,0:13:00.13,Normal,,0,0,0,,Quivering
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.13,0:13:02.30,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(999,926)}"Half a day"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.28,0:13:01.50,Endo,,0,0,0,,Half day
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.50,0:13:04.88,Normal,,0,0,0,,And then he-- all time---
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.88,0:13:08.34,Normal,,0,0,0,,When he turned around, no one was there
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.58,0:13:10.34,Normal,,0,0,0,,There was just a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.70,0:13:13.20,Normal,,0,0,0,,Which was pulling his dress
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.48,0:13:16.08,Normal,,0,0,0,,This is not a story to laugh about
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.08,0:13:23.05,Normal,,0,0,0,,When he got back home, all the houses in the village were burnt in a violent fire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:25.22,Normal,,0,0,0,,It's over
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.22,0:13:30.90,Hosei,,0,0,0,,It was kinda scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:34.50,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,928)}It had a sort of double turn
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.18,0:13:34.50,Hosei,,0,0,0,,Yeah, kinda
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.86,0:13:39.27,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,928)}But in a way it has{\blur3\c&H1435EA&\3c&HFFFFFF&} a happy end,{\r} didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.60,0:13:38.26,Hosei,,0,0,0,,H-happy...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.27,0:13:42.00,Hosei,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,928)\blur3\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&H11980D&}It's not a happy{\r} story, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.72,0:13:46.31,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,What the-?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.14,0:13:46.31,Endo,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.31,0:13:49.05,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,928)}Is him our most non-responding guest or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.62,0:13:53.98,Normal,,0,0,0,,Next up is a scary story from Nigeria, Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:03.18,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Nice dress
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.18,0:14:07.43,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Our representative from Nigeria is Mr. Bobby Ologon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:07.43,Other2,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,0)\pos(775.5,924)}Bobby Ologon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:07.43,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\c&HBABAB8&\fade(250,0)\pos(783,824)}Nigeria Representative
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.66,0:14:11.42,Normal,,0,0,0,,Nigeria is the most populated country in Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.76,0:14:17.41,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H010053&\fade(250,0)\pos(732,914)}Nigeria
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.60,0:14:17.41,Other3,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\move(1000.5,590,862.5,590,16,9785)}Which scary story...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.42,0:14:17.12,Normal,,0,0,0,,Which scary story is from this country of repeated civil wars?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.42,0:14:20.36,Normal,,0,0,0,,Thank you for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.42,0:14:28.30,Normal,,0,0,0,,This is a real scary story which is\Nstill happening in Nigeria nowadays
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.58,0:14:31.78,Normal,,0,0,0,,Its name is "elbowrun granny"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.10,0:14:36.86,Normal,,0,0,0,,The elbowrun granny is really fast
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.06,0:14:40.46,Normal,,0,0,0,,It's said to be faster than a Ferrari
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:44.80,Normal,,0,0,0,,It's a granny who could run up to 300km/h
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.20,0:14:50.84,Normal,,0,0,0,,This granny's story started a long time ago,\Nwhen she married a king
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.67,0:17:12.35,Other1,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,0)\pos(406.5,950)}300kmh fast granny
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.20,0:14:53.36,Normal,,0,0,0,,This king
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.22,0:14:56.48,Normal,,0,0,0,,He was kind to her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.48,0:15:01.86,Normal,,0,0,0,,And still, he eventually got a second wife
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:05.78,Normal,,0,0,0,,But after he got married
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.78,0:15:09.90,Normal,,0,0,0,,He grew distant from his first wife
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.23,0:15:14.62,Normal,,0,0,0,,And told her "just focus on the task I give you"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.62,0:15:16.80,Normal,,0,0,0,,So she went for a 20km walk
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.12,0:15:19.52,Normal,,0,0,0,,In order to get some water
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.98,0:15:23.22,Normal,,0,0,0,,One day, on her road to get water
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.22,0:15:25.78,Normal,,0,0,0,,She slipped
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.78,0:15:27.78,Normal,,0,0,0,,And fell down a cliff
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.02,0:15:30.30,Normal,,0,0,0,,When she fell down
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.30,0:15:32.60,Normal,,0,0,0,,Her body was cut in half
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.60,0:15:36.88,Normal,,0,0,0,,But no one couldn't find her for three whole days
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.36,0:15:40.16,Normal,,0,0,0,,And so she disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.78,0:15:43.79,Normal,,0,0,0,,And became tainted with rage
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:46.94,Normal,,0,0,0,,As she became angrier and angrier
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.94,0:15:52.26,Normal,,0,0,0,,She started to kill everyone from the village
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.26,0:15:58.44,Normal,,0,0,0,,Who came to the river to get water
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.00,0:16:03.02,Normal,,0,0,0,,Her speed was over 300 km/h
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:07.44,Normal,,0,0,0,,And if she goes lock-on on you, you couldn't escape from her
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.76,0:16:09.94,Normal,,0,0,0,,One after another
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.94,0:16:12.96,Normal,,0,0,0,,She started to kill every young men from the village
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.14,0:16:16.86,Normal,,0,0,0,,And so young men started disappearing from the village
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.86,0:16:20.62,Normal,,0,0,0,,And people thought "this is bad, the King has to do something"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.62,0:16:25.74,Normal,,0,0,0,,So they decided to go see the fortune-teller old lady
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.28,0:16:28.68,Normal,,0,0,0,,The old fortune-teller
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.68,0:16:32.84,Normal,,0,0,0,,Said "your previous wife is filled with rage"
